
Make Bootdisk
	mkbootdisk -device /dev/fd0 [kernal number] 
	kernel number eg. 2.2.12-20 - found in /lib/modules]


Archiving utilities:
	cpio - 	available on RH - archiver like tar but more reliable
		Use -depth flag for 'find' when fining lists of files to archive.
	afio - 	compression & archiving, compresses individual files instead
		whole files (safer).
	taper	backup system


Keep copies of:
/etc/fstab
output of 'fdisk -l' (partition table)


Utilities
Partition Image (partimage) - save and restore partition images to compressed files.  Supports all Linux filesystems + experimental NTFS.  Use to do multiple installations.  On Knoppix CD.


